==English==
===Etymology===
Anglo-Saxon ''[[handcops]]''; ''hand'' = hand + ''[[cosp]]'', ''[[cops]]'' = [[fetter]]. The second part was confused with English "[[cuff]]s" ''or'' from "[[hand]]" and "[[cuff]]"

===Noun===
'''handcuffs''' ''Plural'' (Singular:'' '''[[handcuff]]''')

#A fastening, consisting of an iron ring around the wrist, usually connected by a chain or hinge with one on the other wrist; locking rings made of metal and often joined by a chain or hinge which are placed around a prisoner's wrists to make it harder for them to escape or fight; a manacle; -- 
[[handcuffs|usually in the plural]].

